╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  HELIX TRAINER — Exercise 10.2: Structure Navigation            ║
║  Category: Unimpaired            Difficulty: ★★★ Advanced       ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMMANDS TO LEARN
─────────────────
  ] c     Go to next git hunk (change)
  [ c     Go to previous git hunk
  ] T     Go to next test
  [ T     Go to previous test
  ] p     Go to next paragraph
  [ p     Go to previous paragraph
  ] g     Go to next change
  [ g     Go to previous change
  ] G     Go to last change
  [ G     Go to first change
  ] Space Insert empty line below
  [ Space Insert empty line above

INSTRUCTIONS
────────────
  Part A: Add empty lines between each section heading using
  ] Space and [ Space.

  Part B: Fill in the remaining reference entries.

────────────────────────── PRACTICE ──────────────────────────────

SECTION ONE
Content of section one goes here.
SECTION TWO
Content of section two goes here.
SECTION THREE
Content of section three goes here.

MORE NAVIGATION:
  Next git hunk:              ???
  Previous git hunk:          ???
  Next test:                  ???
  Previous test:              ???
  Insert empty line below:    ???
  Insert empty line above:    ???

────────────────────────── EXPECTED ──────────────────────────────

SECTION ONE
Content of section one goes here.

SECTION TWO
Content of section two goes here.

SECTION THREE
Content of section three goes here.

MORE NAVIGATION:
  Next git hunk:              ] c
  Previous git hunk:          [ c
  Next test:                  ] T
  Previous test:              [ T
  Insert empty line below:    ] Space
  Insert empty line above:    [ Space

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HINTS (read only if stuck):
  Hint 1: Position cursor at the end of "section one goes here."
          then press ] Space to insert an empty line below.
  Hint 2: Repeat between each section.
  Hint 3: c=change/hunk, T=test (uppercase), Space=empty line
